This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it discusses the inference of deep neural networks on mobile and embedded devices, which is a common application of computer vision. It is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as deep neural networks are a popular machine learning technique used in AI applications. The neural engineering (cs.NE) sub-category is also a possibility as it deals with the design and implementation of neural networks. Finally, the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category is a possibility as the paper discusses strategies for efficient memory management, which is a common challenge in distributed computing.
